modules.description: Provides functions for analyzing model behavior, generating adversarial examples, and evaluating robustness metrics. Operates on neural network models, input datasets, and performance evaluation results. Used to test model resilience against perturbations and quantify safety guarantees.

Provides a structured interface for working with ONNX models by defining input and output counts and representing model intermediates. Key data types include model metadata and intermediate tensors, with operations for inspecting and manipulating these elements. Users can query the number of inputs and outputs, and access internal representations for further processing. Example tasks include validating model structure and extracting intermediate results for analysis.
